@section(Limiting Factor of Vegetation Growth)

@section(Nitrogen Limiting Factor)

The "Nitrogen VegetationLimitingFactor causing Vegetation Growth" model of Nitrogen module limits the plant growth according to the nitrogen uptaked. This coefficient is in a range between 0 and 1 . Zero indicates lack of nitrogen causing the absence of growth while one indicates that the situation is optimal and consequently, the real growth is equal to the potential growth (if there is no other limitation).

